<Base title="About — poptyping" bodyClass="read-mode">

  <div class="article-crumb-bar">
    <div class="article-crumb-inner">
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">← Home</a>
        <span class="sep">/</span>
        <span>About</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <header class="article-head static-head">
    <h1 class="article-headline">About <em>poptyping</em></h1>
  </header>

  <article class="article-body static-body">
    <p>Poptyping (Welsh for <em>microwave</em>) is a satirical news publication that reheats current affairs into something that might be funnier, and is definitely shorter.</p>

    <p><strong>Reheated Goodness.</strong></p>

    <p>Founded in 2026 by people who should know better, poptyping covers the topics other publications cover — but with worse intentions and fewer fact-checkers.</p>

    <p>No subscriptions. No paywall. No standards.</p>

    <h2>The rules</h2>

    <p>All headlines are fictitious. Any resemblance to actual events, persons, or institutions is coincidental — and, given the state of things, increasingly difficult to maintain.</p>

    <p>We don't write about private individuals. We don't write about anyone's family. We don't punch down. Everything else is fair game.</p>

    <h2>Get in touch</h2>

    <p>Tips, complaints, marriage proposals: <a href="mailto:hello@poptyping.com">hello@poptyping.com</a></p>

    <div class="article-end">END</div>
  </article>

</Base>
